            <section id="anglr-language-syntax">
                <h1>Anglr Syntax Rules for ASN.1 Language</h1>
                <hr />
                <h4>Introduction</h4>
                <p>
                    This paragraph contains Anglr syntax rules for ASN.1 and basic SNMP macros. If we translate this text using an ANGLR compiler, we get the source code for the ASN.1 parser.
                </p>
                <hr />
                <h4>Syntax</h4>
                <div class="panel border bg-light">
                    <pre>
<span class="attribute-brace">[</span> <span class="attribute-name" id="Description">Description</span> <span class="attribute-val-name" id="Text">Text</span><span class="def-separator">=</span><span class="attribute-val-value">&#39;Declarations&#39;</span> <span class="attribute-val-name" id="Hover">Hover</span><span class="def-separator">=</span><span class="attribute-val-value">&#39;false&#39;</span> <span class="attribute-brace">]</span>
